The '''Supreme Commander of the Republic Military''' was the title given to the head of the [[Republic Military/Legends|Republic Military]]. During the [[Cold War (Galactic Republic–Sith Empire)|Cold War]], it was held by the [[Duros/Legends|Duros]] [[Stantorrs]]. With the beginning of the [[Galactic War]], the title passed to [[Jace Malcom]]. [[19 BBY/Legends|Millennia]] later, before the [[Mission to Mustafar/Legends|end]] of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] the [[Galactic Senate/Legends|Senate]] enacted the [[Security Act amendment]], making [[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Chancellor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] the Supreme Commander. It gave him constitutional authority over the Republic Armed Forces, stripping it away from the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi]] and the Senate. This authority allowed Palpatine to issue [[Order 66/Legends|Order 66]], and remain as the commander-in-chief of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] as the [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]].

